Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Pop the @British Chicken Breasts{2} into a large #bowl{} along with the @Ginger, Garlic & Lemongrass Puree{15%g} and @Oil for the Chicken{1/2}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, mix well, then set aside.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw chicken and its packaging.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{1} in a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Once hot, lay the chicken flat in the pan. Season with salt and pepper and fry until browned on each side and cooked through, ~{13-15%minutes}. Turn every ~{2-3%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: The chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Meanwhile, peel and grate the @garlic clove{2} (or use a #garlic press{}). Tear the @ciabatta{1} into roughly 2cm chunks.

Pop the ciabatta onto a #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{for the croutons}, season with salt and pepper, add the garlic and toss to coat.

Bake the croutons on the middle shelf until golden, ~{8-10%minutes}, then remove from the oven and set aside.

While the chicken and croutons cook, trim and peel the @carrot{1}. Use the #peeler{} to peel long ribbons down the length of the carrot, stopping at the core.

Halve the @baby plum tomatoes{125%g}. Crush the @salted peanuts{25%g} in the unopened sachet using a #rolling pin{}.

In a small bowl, combine the @mayonnaise{32%g}, @water for the mayo{1/2}, and @sambal paste{15%g}, then set aside.

In another large bowl, mix together the @rice vinegar{15%g}, @olive oil for the dressing{1}, and @sugar for the dressing{1}. Season with salt and pepper.

Add the tomatoes into the bowl with the rice vinegar dressing and mix together.

When everything's ready, add the @baby leaf mix{50%g}, carrot ribbons and croutons to the bowl of tomatoes. Toss together and share out between your #serving bowls{}.

Thinly slice the chicken and divide it between your bowls, then serve on top of your salad.

Scatter over the peanuts and drizzle over the sambal mayo to finish.

Enjoy!